  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-629927a9-7fff-b0f1-07bd-c10649a3087a\" dir=\"ltr\">This simple iron flask is filled with water when found, water with a slightly sweet taste. The flask generates up to one half gallon of water each day, enough to keep one person alive as long as they aren't exceptionally active. Once per day, as an action, its owner can attempt an itelligence (arcana) check to transmute the water into one of the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A @Compendium[dnd5e.items.ytlsBjYsZ7OBSEBs]{Potion of Healing} (DC 10)</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A @Compendium[dnd5e.items.L887NdWEP5NqHCrQ]{Potion of Greater Healing} (DC 15)</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A @Compendium[dnd5e.items.Jj4iFQQGvckx8Wsj]{Potion of Fire Resistance} (DC 20) (or a similar potion that grants resistance to another damage type)</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A @Compendium[dnd5e.items.wNKYbKYwOHbA7SH8]{Potion of Heroism} (DC 25)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once the potion is consumed, further liquid produced that day is nonmagical. Any potion produced in this way loses its magical properties the following dawn.</p>",
